[The Last Request]


163
00:11:07,660 --> 00:11:11,930
[The Last Request]


164
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,940
[Episode 9]


165
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:20,070
[That woman took Yi-chan.]


166
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:23,610
Please check in on him
and see how he's doing.


167
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:32,550
Good morning, guys.


168
00:11:34,390 --> 00:11:36,590
-My gosh. Hello, Mr. Oh.
-Hello.


169
00:11:36,890 --> 00:11:38,830
-Good morning, Mr. Danny.
-Good morning, Mr. Danny.


170
00:11:38,930 --> 00:11:41,830
How come
you two came to school together today?


171
00:11:42,860 --> 00:11:45,070
Yi-chan's mother had something
to take care of.


172
00:11:45,130 --> 00:11:47,100
His mom is at the police station now.


173
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:50,470
That's why
he slept at our place last night. Right?


174
00:11:50,970 --> 00:11:52,140
I see.


175
00:11:54,010 --> 00:11:57,180
-Did you sleep well at Jae-in's place?
-Yes.


176
00:11:57,610 --> 00:11:59,050
Mr. Danny.


177
00:11:59,410 --> 00:12:02,120
Can my mom not get out soon this time?


178
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,720
Since you're doing so well,


179
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:11,360
your mom will be released very soon.


180
00:12:12,060 --> 00:12:14,560
All right.
Shall I take you to your classroom?


181
00:12:14,630 --> 00:12:15,700
-Yes.
-Yes.


182
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:17,770
I'll take the kids inside.


183
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:19,330
Would you?


184
00:12:19,730 --> 00:12:22,540
I have to stop by the security office
to check on something for Jae-in.


185
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,000
Let's go, kids.


186
00:12:24,170 --> 00:12:26,070
-Have fun. I'll pick you up later.
-Say bye.


187
00:12:26,140 --> 00:12:27,810
-Let's go.
-Bye.


188
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:29,080
Thank you.


189
00:12:35,950 --> 00:12:39,590
We were delayed
because of the passing of Chairman Doh.


190
00:12:41,620 --> 00:12:42,860
This is it here.


191
00:12:50,330 --> 00:12:51,970
What is Jae-in doing there?


192
00:13:16,260 --> 00:13:17,960
Jae-in really did this?


193
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,000
Ms. Hwang Na-yoon?


194
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:31,910
May I have a word with you?


195
00:13:34,010 --> 00:13:35,110
Sure.


196
00:13:36,610 --> 00:13:39,880
We arrested Ms. Song
based on the circumstantial evidence


197
00:13:39,950 --> 00:13:42,320
and your statement,


198
00:13:43,020 --> 00:13:46,090
but something is just not adding up.


199
00:13:46,420 --> 00:13:47,720
What do you mean?


200
00:13:47,790 --> 00:13:52,130
You said you overheard
Ms. Song and Chairman Doh's argument.


201
00:13:52,190 --> 00:13:53,960
Then the two of them


202
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:56,960
went to Chairman Doh's office
and kept on arguing.


203
00:13:57,030 --> 00:14:00,770
And in the end, Chairman Doh
took her drugged drink and collapsed.


204
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:04,340
Doesn't that sound unnatural?


205
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,410
I'm not sure what you mean.


206
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,680
My question is,


207
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,680
if you saw the two of them fight


208
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:13,050
before Chairman Doh died,


209
00:14:13,110 --> 00:14:14,520
why didn't you try to stop them?


210
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:17,020
I'm sure you had enough time to stop them.


211
00:14:17,950 --> 00:14:19,650
-That's--
-If you gave a false statement


212
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:22,660
because of your relationship
with Ms. Song,


213
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,230
you can be charged.


214
00:14:27,930 --> 00:14:30,300
Are you saying that I'm lying?


215
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:34,030
You shouldn't deviate from the truth
just because of your personal feelings.


216
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,570
And what you saw
in the security office just now


217
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:40,070
was also not what you had thought,
wasn't it?


218
00:14:40,910 --> 00:14:43,040
I did not lie.


219
00:14:43,140 --> 00:14:46,110
She was the last to see my husband
and the chairman alive.


220
00:14:46,180 --> 00:14:47,250
And that woman


221
00:14:47,410 --> 00:14:49,820
even threatened to harm me.


222
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:50,850
Ms. Hwang.


223
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:53,790
Will you be responsible
if something happens to me?


224
00:14:53,850 --> 00:14:56,590
What will you do
if she tries to harm Jae-in?


225
00:15:02,830 --> 00:15:04,030
It smells so good.


226
00:15:18,650 --> 00:15:19,850
Mr. Oh?


227
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:27,490
I didn't expect you'd still be here.


228
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,760
I thought you should be heading back


229
00:15:29,820 --> 00:15:32,090
to Toronto now that the funeral is over.


230
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:34,630
-Excuse me?
-You're excused.


231
00:15:35,060 --> 00:15:37,160
I know you handed in your resignation.


232
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:41,500
Well, about that.
Yes, but it was rejected.


233
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,800
Oh, then...


234
00:15:44,140 --> 00:15:45,740
You should send it to me again.


235
00:15:46,610 --> 00:15:50,310
Indeed. But I've changed my mind.


236
00:15:50,410 --> 00:15:52,310
You know, the kids like me a lot.


237
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,380
Listen. I know why Ms. Doh employed you.


238
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:58,990
But I'm different.


239
00:15:59,290 --> 00:16:01,620
And this is no place
for a person like you.


240
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:03,820
We both know


241
00:16:03,890 --> 00:16:05,790
you don't want the cops sniffing around.


242
00:16:06,790 --> 00:16:09,360
They will be coming for you next.


243
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,570
Yes, seems like it.


244
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:15,640
But it's not like
I'm the only one who will be in trouble.


245
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:19,210
What do you mean by that?


246
00:16:20,210 --> 00:16:23,880
Anyway, thanks for your advice.


247
00:16:27,850 --> 00:16:30,480
By the way, you still owe me a game.


248
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:32,590
You can skate now, right?


249
00:16:33,090 --> 00:16:34,050
Then,


250
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:37,790
see you on the ice.


251
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,970
[What is wrong with you?]


252
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,140
You idiot, I should just...


253
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:53,540
Darn it!


254
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:56,910
[Police Charter]


255
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,010
[Chief Yoo Tae-hwan]


256
00:17:00,610 --> 00:17:02,780
As you know,
we were told to close the case


257
00:17:02,850 --> 00:17:04,390
as a cardiac arrest.


258
00:17:04,450 --> 00:17:06,250
But you insisted


259
00:17:06,690 --> 00:17:09,260
on arresting her without a warrant
and even searched her home.


260
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:11,760
What now? What will you do?


261
00:17:11,829 --> 00:17:14,190
You messed with the school
and even with their lawyer!


262
00:17:16,530 --> 00:17:17,599
I apologize.


263
00:17:17,930 --> 00:17:20,030
-Please give me some time to--
-As if!


264
00:17:24,609 --> 00:17:25,670
Fine.


265
00:17:25,940 --> 00:17:28,510
Are you trying to use this case


266
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:30,310
to go back to Seoul?


267
00:17:31,780 --> 00:17:33,280
No. Of course not.


268
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:35,420
-The case is still--
-I don't want to hear it!


269
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:39,890
Wrap up the case right now. You got that?


270
00:17:39,990 --> 00:17:41,920
You were sent here from Seoul
because you got demoted.


271
00:17:41,990 --> 00:17:43,260
So don't cause trouble, okay?


272
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:48,230
Mr. Gu, this town is not
the kind of place you think it is.


273
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,730
You got it all wrong!


274
00:17:50,230 --> 00:17:51,470
Do you understand?


275
00:17:52,570 --> 00:17:53,630
Yes, sir.


276
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:59,910
[Violent Crimes 1]


277
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,680
Did you get chewed out?


278
00:17:59,970 --> 00:18:05,350
[Violent Crimes 1]


279
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,410
Does Chief want us off the case?


280
00:18:06,310 --> 00:18:07,750
Don't worry about it.


281
00:18:08,380 --> 00:18:12,350
Right. About Nam Ji-seon,
the CEO of Locanda Jeju.


282
00:18:12,420 --> 00:18:13,820
-What's going on?
-Sorry?


283
00:18:15,390 --> 00:18:16,460
We're not there yet.


284
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:17,890
What have you been doing?


285
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:20,860
If we can't get Song Yeo-wool,
we have to try other ways.


286
00:18:20,930 --> 00:18:21,960
Right.


287
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:26,030
Bring Nam Ji-seon in for an interview.


288
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:40,380
We're letting you go,
but I'm sure you know that it doesn't mean


289
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:42,020
you're off the hook.


290
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,350
We will bring you back in
whenever we need to.


291
00:18:44,550 --> 00:18:45,890
Sure, knock yourself out.


292
00:18:46,590 --> 00:18:49,490
But you couldn't find anything
even with me in the cell,


293
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:51,930
so I doubt you'll find anything new.


294
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:57,000
You'd better watch out.


295
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:03,370
Once I bite, I never let go.


296
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:10,610
[Interview Room]


297
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,410
Hey, you.


298
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,750
Hey, you.


299
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:26,190
Oh, my.


300
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:29,830
I never imagined
I'd be waiting for someone here.


301
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:32,800
And not even once. Twice.


302
00:19:32,870 --> 00:19:33,870
You're right.


303
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,240
Thank you.


304
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,740
I'm glad you were released quickly.


305
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,210
You went through a lot.


306
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:44,180
What about Yi-chan?
Let's go pick him up first.


307
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:46,750
It's still long before school gets out.


308
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:49,150
Did you eat?


309
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:53,890
I know a really good seafood stew place.


310
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:57,890
Should I get you some soy sauce?


311
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,460
-No, we're good. Thank you.
-All right.


312
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:06,230
Dig in. I asked the owner
to prepare it especially for you.


313
00:20:07,330 --> 00:20:09,800
Is it because
you didn't have this last time?


314
00:20:09,870 --> 00:20:12,310
You don't look like you would've been
to the police often.


315
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:15,380
I forgot you're a lawyer.


316
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:16,840
I went there often because of work.


317
00:20:16,910 --> 00:20:19,510
Anyway, you wouldn't have gone
for personal--


318
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:22,150
No, you did.


319
00:20:22,220 --> 00:20:24,420
This is my third time now.


320
00:20:27,190 --> 00:20:28,360
That reminds me.


321
00:20:30,590 --> 00:20:33,590
Here. I kept it safe,
like you wanted me to.


322
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,930
And from now on, only contact me


323
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,170
through Oh Soon-sang's phone.


324
00:20:41,370 --> 00:20:42,440
Okay.


325
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:45,940
Let's eat first.


326
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:54,580
Slow down. You'll get an upset stomach.


327
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:01,220
I have to hurry up and go get Yi-chan.


328
00:21:08,130 --> 00:21:11,230
Even before anyone can talk,


329
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:12,570
you're already impatient.


330
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:32,490
-Yi-chan.
-Mom!


331
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:34,250
My gosh.


332
00:21:35,890 --> 00:21:37,390
How have you been, son?


333
00:21:37,860 --> 00:21:40,560
Mom, what took you so long?


334
00:21:40,630 --> 00:21:43,130
Do you know how much I missed you?


335
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,300
Right. I'm sorry.


336
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:47,770
Let's see.


337
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:51,040
You look like you've grown a lot
since the last time I saw you.


338
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:53,370
I had a great time at Jae-in's house.


339
00:21:53,670 --> 00:21:56,080
Jae-in's mom cooked us
lots of delicious food.


340
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:58,580
You're really brave.


341
00:21:59,780 --> 00:22:02,450
-Jae-in.
-Mom!


342
00:22:07,550 --> 00:22:09,720
Yi-chan had fun with us at our house.


343
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:15,900
Making a false statement
and even taking my kid without permission.


344
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:18,270
Get ready to be sued
for false accusations.


345
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:19,930
I guess you don't need me
to settle with you.


346
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,900
I've already been to jail once.
Twice isn't hard.


347
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:26,070
Let me remind you. Don't you dare
show yourself in front of us again.


348
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:28,580
Do you understand what I mean?


349
00:22:53,230 --> 00:22:55,140
-Yi-chan.
-Yes?


350
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:58,070
Did you have a good time
with Jae-in and her mom?


351
00:22:58,340 --> 00:23:02,080
Yes. But it wasn't fun at all without you.


352
00:23:02,410 --> 00:23:04,640
Really?


353
00:23:06,680 --> 00:23:09,920
I'll sing you a song
so listen to it as you watch the stars.


354
00:23:09,980 --> 00:23:10,980
Okay.


355
00:23:11,950 --> 00:23:18,290
♫ Twinkle, twinkle, little star ♫


356
00:23:19,090 --> 00:23:25,230
♫ How I wonder what you are ♫


357
00:23:27,530 --> 00:23:30,770
Mom, the sky is really filled with stars.


358
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:32,770
Right?


359
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:38,180
Mom, do you see that shining star?
What's that called?


360
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:40,410
That's the North Star.


361
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,550
The North Star?


362
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,620
If you get lost,


363
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:45,750
you'll be able to find your way
with that star.


364
00:23:45,820 --> 00:23:46,790
Really?


365
00:23:46,990 --> 00:23:49,790
Yes. The North Star doesn't move around.


366
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:52,660
It's always in the same place
in the northern sky.


367
00:23:52,730 --> 00:23:54,900
So if you follow that star,


368
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,800
you'll be walking north.


369
00:23:56,860 --> 00:23:59,870
Really?
I'm going to tell Jae-in about this.


370
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:05,040
It would've been nice if we came
with Jae-in and her mom like last time.


371
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:06,640
Right?


372
00:24:11,210 --> 00:24:12,980
Yi-chan, want me to sing it again?


373
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:22,820
♫ -Twinkle, twinkle, little star
-Twinkle, twinkle, little star ♫


374
00:24:23,690 --> 00:24:30,530
♫ -Twinkle, twinkle, little star
-Twinkle, twinkle, little star ♫


375
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:32,770
I'm not really good at this.


376
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:13,610
Tell me why you lied.


377
00:25:15,510 --> 00:25:18,310
If you didn't want to do it,
you could've just said so.


378
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:20,580
Aren't you going to tell me why?


379
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:23,220
You lied to me too.


380
00:25:24,050 --> 00:25:25,750
Dad didn't come.


381
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:31,990
-Dad told us to come here first.
-You're lying.


382
00:25:32,060 --> 00:25:35,160
Yi-chan told me he can't come.


383
00:25:35,330 --> 00:25:36,700
And that I can't see him again.


384
00:25:39,430 --> 00:25:42,470
-Jae-in.
-Do you know how much I miss Dad?


385
00:25:42,870 --> 00:25:44,200
I hate you.


386
00:25:54,410 --> 00:25:58,750
Jae-in, I thought Dad


387
00:25:59,820 --> 00:26:01,490
was definitely going to come


388
00:26:02,590 --> 00:26:04,960
to see the both of us one day.


389
00:26:05,660 --> 00:26:07,760
Dad would never break a promise.


390
00:26:09,060 --> 00:26:12,470
So I wanted to show Dad


391
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:15,170
what Jae-in was great at.


392
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:24,340
I'm sorry.


393
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:29,450
I didn't mean to lie to you.


394
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:31,320
I also miss Dad


395
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:34,750
as much as you miss him.


396
00:26:37,320 --> 00:26:38,660
Mom.


397
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:42,860
I'm sorry too.


398
00:26:45,970 --> 00:26:47,470
Please forgive me.


399
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:05,220
What is it? Did you get anything?


400
00:27:05,450 --> 00:27:06,620
Sir.


401
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,360
Thank you.


402
00:27:10,420 --> 00:27:11,490
Sir.


403
00:27:11,690 --> 00:27:15,060
This is the CCTV on the second floor
of the central hallway


404
00:27:15,130 --> 00:27:17,500
half an hour before the blackout
from 6:40 p.m. to 7:10 p.m.


405
00:27:18,030 --> 00:27:19,070
Take a look.


406
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,200
What is this?


407
00:27:26,070 --> 00:27:29,980
So this is why
she couldn't give us an alibi.


408
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,550
Hold on.


409
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:36,650
If it takes at least 30 minutes


410
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:38,690
for the drug to take effect...


411
00:27:39,550 --> 00:27:42,520
What time did we get the 911 call
from the chairman's office?


412
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:45,060
It was 7:45 p.m.


413
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:50,330
That means she wasn't there at that time.


414
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:55,070
-What should we do?
-I'll take care of this.


415
00:27:55,140 --> 00:27:57,970
You call Nam Ji-seon in first, stat.


416
00:27:58,040 --> 00:27:59,140
Yes, sir.


417
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:07,210
Starting next Monday,


418
00:28:07,310 --> 00:28:09,720
we'll be taking a vacation
to Hawaii for two weeks.


419
00:28:10,180 --> 00:28:11,690
Keep that in mind.


420
00:28:12,690 --> 00:28:15,820
Really? We're going to Hawaii?


421
00:28:16,060 --> 00:28:17,560
What about school then?


422
00:28:17,890 --> 00:28:19,160
Missing a few days is fine.


423
00:28:19,230 --> 00:28:21,030
-I'll let the school know.
-Okay.


424
00:28:21,090 --> 00:28:23,330
What do you mean by a vacation?
It's so out of the blue.


425
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:24,800
There's the incident at the school...


426
00:28:26,470 --> 00:28:28,600
and the police investigation.
It's all a bit messy.


427
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:30,300
Take a rest with the kids


428
00:28:30,370 --> 00:28:32,340
until everything settles down.


429
00:28:32,970 --> 00:28:34,910
You should refresh yourself as well.


430
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:37,980
But I already have surgeries


431
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,710
and golf games scheduled during that time.


432
00:28:39,950 --> 00:28:42,220
You can't miss out on a family vacation.


433
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,720
We have to go together.


434
00:28:43,980 --> 00:28:46,620
I'll tell the hospital to reschedule
the surgeries with another doctor.


435
00:28:46,690 --> 00:28:49,260
The hospital will be fine without you


436
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:51,160
and you can postpone
the golf games, right?


437
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:55,130
What is it? Is there something else?


438
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,760
No.


439
00:28:57,660 --> 00:29:00,330
I got it. I'll take a look at my schedule.


440
00:29:01,230 --> 00:29:02,300
I'm off.


441
00:29:04,300 --> 00:29:05,840
Bye, Dad.


442
00:29:27,490 --> 00:29:29,530
After making that mess at the funeral,


443
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:31,260
you even got arrested yourself.


444
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:35,300
Wouldn't it be right for you to step down
as the school's legal advisor?


445
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:37,600
At the funeral, you told me


446
00:29:37,700 --> 00:29:40,040
that I've still got a long way to go.


447
00:29:40,170 --> 00:29:41,210
Did I?


448
00:29:41,340 --> 00:29:44,780
But I may not have
such a long way to go after all.


449
00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:48,750
I told the police everything I know.


450
00:29:48,820 --> 00:29:49,880
Well...


451
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:53,750
I doubt I'll be questioned by the police
like a certain someone.


452
00:29:59,590 --> 00:30:02,630
The police would like to interview you
as a witness.


453
00:30:02,760 --> 00:30:05,000
I'm late for my breakfast meeting.
Let's go.


454
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:24,580
What a lonely death


455
00:30:24,850 --> 00:30:26,390
for someone who held such a high position.


456
00:30:26,620 --> 00:30:29,290
She didn't know many people
in Korea, but still.


457
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,860
What brings you here?


458
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:34,490
Why didn't you tell me the truth?


459
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:37,860
That you were with Mr. Danny Oh that day
at the time of the incident.


460
00:30:38,430 --> 00:30:41,500
If you'd told me,
you wouldn't have been suspected.


461
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:45,070
What were you trying to hide
by going to all this trouble?


462
00:30:45,140 --> 00:30:48,480
It's just that I left out
anything unrelated to the case.


463
00:30:49,010 --> 00:30:50,580
"Unrelated"?


464
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:54,610
Lat time, your missing husband
was assumed to have committed suicide,


465
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:57,880
and now, the chairman is assumed
to have been murdered.


466
00:30:58,450 --> 00:31:01,020
Two mysterious incidents
have happened around you


467
00:31:01,090 --> 00:31:03,290
one year apart.


468
00:31:04,220 --> 00:31:06,130
Was it just a coincidence?


469
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:07,890
Please don't jump to conclusions.


470
00:31:08,460 --> 00:31:10,860
Are you implying that I killed them both?


471
00:31:10,930 --> 00:31:12,600
Well, it wouldn't have been impossible


472
00:31:13,100 --> 00:31:16,040
with the help of someone.


473
00:31:19,410 --> 00:31:21,010
Both then and now,


474
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:24,010
why are you so obsessed with me?


475
00:31:24,610 --> 00:31:26,680
Why must you dig up the case
from a year ago?


476
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,920
No less than 300 billion won
vanished into thin air


477
00:31:30,980 --> 00:31:33,790
at the same time as your husband's death.


478
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:36,620
The victims left behind
are still suffering.


479
00:31:38,260 --> 00:31:40,330
Let's say you really have


480
00:31:40,390 --> 00:31:42,100
nothing to do with that incident.


481
00:31:42,460 --> 00:31:45,600
But are you really going to
just stand by and watch?


482
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:49,540
Don't you feel the least bit responsible?


483
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:53,510
That's not okay with me.


484
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:03,350
-It's me.
[-Captain.]


485
00:32:03,420 --> 00:32:05,890
[We're done analyzing the fingerprints
from the circuit breaker.]


486
00:32:05,950 --> 00:32:06,990
Really?


487
00:32:07,390 --> 00:32:08,560
Have they been identified?


488
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:10,190
Who?


489
00:32:11,590 --> 00:32:13,460
Okay. I'll be right there.


490
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:28,610
[Salon de Ae]


491
00:32:30,610 --> 00:32:32,310
Why is there a police car...


492
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:33,910
[Salon de Ae]


493
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,430
Mr. Jung Mi-do?


494
00:32:54,270 --> 00:32:57,040
Your name appears many times
in the chairman's call history.


495
00:32:57,100 --> 00:32:59,670
What was your relationship with her?


496
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:04,540
How does my offer sound?


497
00:33:05,140 --> 00:33:08,880
I'll sort out the matter
with the restaurant for you.


498
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:11,480
You have nothing to lose, right?


499
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:14,390
Deal.


500
00:33:14,790 --> 00:33:18,160
But is that really all I need to do?


501
00:33:18,790 --> 00:33:23,230
For a start, how about we send
some flowers to her?


502
00:33:23,730 --> 00:33:25,100
To welcome her.


503
00:33:26,930 --> 00:33:28,130
All right.


504
00:33:28,940 --> 00:33:31,970
Anyway, I trust you.


505
00:33:32,810 --> 00:33:35,610
Also, I'm sure you already know this,


506
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:39,180
but this stays between us, okay?


507
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:43,380
If you behave.


508
00:33:45,390 --> 00:33:46,920
[She was an old friend of mine.]


509
00:33:47,050 --> 00:33:49,790
She helped me out many times
when I was in a pinch.


510
00:33:52,690 --> 00:33:55,600
We found your fingerprints
on the circuit breaker


511
00:33:55,660 --> 00:33:57,700
in the school's generator room.


512
00:33:57,800 --> 00:33:59,670
Can you explain?


513
00:34:03,770 --> 00:34:05,240
Did you kill the chairman?


514
00:34:05,870 --> 00:34:08,170
No, never.


515
00:34:08,940 --> 00:34:10,440
Then what is it?


516
00:34:10,610 --> 00:34:12,909
You're not even a parent.
Why would you attend a school concert


517
00:34:12,980 --> 00:34:14,310
and cut off electricity?


518
00:34:17,820 --> 00:34:19,650
I was invited.


519
00:34:20,150 --> 00:34:23,989
But we'd been having a bit of a conflict
over investments lately.


520
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:27,429
Sitting there with them
in that situation...


521
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:32,969
-Look at our son.
-I know.


522
00:34:34,270 --> 00:34:37,670
-He's so good.
-Yes.


523
00:34:47,449 --> 00:34:50,420
[Automatic control panel,
Main]


524
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:54,750
[Automatic control panel,
Main]


525
00:34:54,719 --> 00:34:55,860
[It was an impulse.]


526
00:34:57,560 --> 00:35:00,260
I lost my temper and acted on impulse.


527
00:35:01,990 --> 00:35:04,430
Then I returned to my car immediately.


528
00:35:04,530 --> 00:35:07,170
You can check my dashcam footage
if you want.


529
00:35:07,500 --> 00:35:08,770
Is that right?


530
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:12,170
Even if you were having a conflict
over a business matter,


531
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:14,710
why would you do such a thing
at a school event?


532
00:35:16,340 --> 00:35:17,780
Tell me the truth.


533
00:35:17,840 --> 00:35:19,550
I can go through


534
00:35:19,810 --> 00:35:21,850
not only your dashcam footage


535
00:35:21,980 --> 00:35:23,480
but also your call and text history.


536
00:35:28,150 --> 00:35:29,620
Yes.


537
00:35:30,190 --> 00:35:31,460
I'm really sorry,


538
00:35:32,460 --> 00:35:35,600
but I'm not in the situation
to meet with anyone right now.


539
00:35:36,860 --> 00:35:40,330
I know we made an appointment, but...


540
00:35:42,300 --> 00:35:43,670
He's in Jeju Island now?


541
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,470
He came all the way here?


542
00:35:46,310 --> 00:35:47,910
[He didn't have to.]


543
00:35:47,970 --> 00:35:50,480
He insists on talking to you in person.


544
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:52,410
[Golden Law Firm]


545
00:35:50,610 --> 00:35:53,010
He says he already knows you.


546
00:35:55,880 --> 00:35:58,150
He knows me?


547
00:35:59,550 --> 00:36:01,220
[Okay, at 7 p.m.?]


548
00:36:01,290 --> 00:36:02,890
All right. I'll be there.


549
00:36:03,290 --> 00:36:04,390
Bye.


550
00:36:10,300 --> 00:36:11,430
Gosh, you scared me.


551
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,770
What is it?


552
00:36:13,030 --> 00:36:14,130
What are you doing?


553
00:36:14,530 --> 00:36:15,940
-Music?
-What?


554
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:18,070
What kind of music do you like?


555
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:27,450
I don't hear anything.


556
00:36:28,450 --> 00:36:30,820
-Is it broken or something?
-Well...


557
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:33,150
It hasn't been working well lately.


558
00:36:33,220 --> 00:36:34,850
Danny, what are you doing later today?


559
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:37,520
It's Friday.
Why don't we grab a beer or something?


560
00:36:37,590 --> 00:36:40,990
Too bad. I already have plans.


561
00:36:41,130 --> 00:36:42,260
I see.


562
00:36:42,730 --> 00:36:44,860
How about next week? It's my treat.


563
00:36:44,930 --> 00:36:46,570
-Next Friday then?
-Okay.


564
00:36:46,630 --> 00:36:48,130
-Are you sure?
-Yes.


565
00:36:48,570 --> 00:36:49,600
Okay.


566
00:36:50,070 --> 00:36:51,600
-I'll keep Friday open.
-Good.


567
00:36:56,710 --> 00:36:58,140
I really can't do this.


568
00:37:08,820 --> 00:37:10,060
Ms. Song Yeo-wool?


569
00:37:14,590 --> 00:37:17,600
Are you the one who wanted to see me?


570
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:29,440
I didn't know you speak Korean.


571
00:37:29,510 --> 00:37:31,640
We don't have to speak English
outside of the school, do we?


572
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:33,580
Fancy a drink?


573
00:37:38,350 --> 00:37:39,950
Single malt on the rocks for me.


574
00:37:41,990 --> 00:37:43,120
I'm fine.


575
00:37:49,730 --> 00:37:51,100
What's the reason


576
00:37:51,460 --> 00:37:53,770
you wanted to see me alone?


577
00:37:57,140 --> 00:37:58,540
Let me introduce myself properly.


578
00:37:58,700 --> 00:38:01,410
I'm Mr. An Ji-yong's accountant
and legal representative,


579
00:38:01,470 --> 00:38:02,780
Alex Cormer.


580
00:38:04,010 --> 00:38:06,450
You're my husband's representative?


581
00:38:13,350 --> 00:38:16,720
Bug her, tail her,
or do whatever it takes.


582
00:38:16,790 --> 00:38:18,520
I need you to report


583
00:38:18,590 --> 00:38:20,690
Song Yeo-wool's every move to me.


584
00:38:20,790 --> 00:38:23,900
-Is that all?
-No.


585
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:26,800
There's one more person
I need you to look into.


586
00:38:26,970 --> 00:38:31,070
A surcharge of 70 percent will be charged
on every additional task.


587
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:34,770
That's nothing you should worry about.


588
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:38,140
Sure. As long as you pay me, why not?


589
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:39,780
By the way,


590
00:38:40,950 --> 00:38:44,180
it seems there are many around you
whom you can't trust,


591
00:38:44,380 --> 00:38:45,580
Ms. Doh.


592
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,290
Who is it this time?


593
00:38:54,660 --> 00:38:56,300
Alex Cormer.


594
00:38:56,730 --> 00:38:59,230
[The school's director of finance.]


595
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:03,440
How am I supposed to believe
that you're my husband's representative?


596
00:39:13,610 --> 00:39:15,880
Happy wedding anniversary.


597
00:39:19,220 --> 00:39:21,150
-Honey.
-Aren't you going to open it?


598
00:39:28,330 --> 00:39:30,500
Mr. An wanted me to give you this.


599
00:39:31,260 --> 00:39:34,030
So, do you believe me now?


600
00:39:51,650 --> 00:39:53,450
Why did you keep this story
from me until now?


601
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:57,320
I kept requesting to meet you
through the law firm.


602
00:39:58,120 --> 00:40:00,160
And it isn't something
to talk about at school.


603
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:09,300
What happened to my husband?


604
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,440
Is he perhaps alive?


605
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:16,510
When did you receive this ring?


606
00:40:16,780 --> 00:40:20,010
On the day of the accident,
Mr. An asked me to deliver this.


607
00:40:20,950 --> 00:40:22,180
Along with it,


608
00:40:22,250 --> 00:40:24,480
he asked me to pass along
a request for you a year after that.


609
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:31,820
What is his request?


610
00:40:44,270 --> 00:40:46,440
It's time to step out of the shadow


611
00:40:46,510 --> 00:40:47,940
of Mr. An's death,


612
00:40:48,010 --> 00:40:49,040
Ms. Song Yeo-wool.


613
00:40:59,890 --> 00:41:01,520
Don't listen to that scumbag.


614
00:41:01,690 --> 00:41:03,820
What? Did you follow me?


615
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:05,590
No, well...


616
00:41:06,160 --> 00:41:08,090
Just don't listen to him.


617
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:10,260
We're not even done talking yet.


618
00:41:10,600 --> 00:41:12,830
Why shouldn't I? What's your reason?


619
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,370
There's another person the chairman


620
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:18,770
wanted me to look into besides you.


621
00:41:18,840 --> 00:41:20,640
And that person is that jerk.


622
00:41:20,840 --> 00:41:22,780
Look into him? Why?


623
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,810
Isn't he close to the chairman?


624
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:26,450
I don't know the reason yet.


625
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:29,250
But something must've been fishy.


626
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:32,750
I got good at reading people
from doing this job,


627
00:41:32,820 --> 00:41:35,860
and there's something
really off about him.


628
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:36,960
He came forth


629
00:41:37,020 --> 00:41:39,490
as your husband's representative
the moment the chairman died.


630
00:41:39,560 --> 00:41:42,090
Anyway, he's not someone you should trust.


631
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:45,160
My head is already on the verge
of explosion without your help, so stop.


632
00:41:45,430 --> 00:41:47,370
From what I see,
you're more unreliable than him,


633
00:41:47,430 --> 00:41:49,840
appearing in front of me
and telling me all this.


634
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:53,370
Am I the one you're doubting right now?


635
00:41:58,610 --> 00:42:00,710
My goodness, I'm losing it.


636
00:42:03,650 --> 00:42:05,890
What do you mean,
I should report my husband's death?


637
00:42:05,950 --> 00:42:08,590
His death was declared
by the police investigation,


638
00:42:08,690 --> 00:42:11,220
but it hasn't been legally processed yet.


639
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:13,090
It's the request of the deceased.


640
00:42:13,930 --> 00:42:16,330
He asks to be freed


641
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,770
and completely forgotten with death.


642
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:25,070
You want me to end it after so long


643
00:42:25,700 --> 00:42:27,340
simply for that reason?


644
00:42:27,410 --> 00:42:29,180
That's not the only reason.


645
00:42:29,710 --> 00:42:31,110
To be honest,


646
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:33,980
you might have not known,


647
00:42:34,980 --> 00:42:37,020
but the foundation and the company have


648
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:38,580
a debt of 500 million dollars.


649
00:42:39,190 --> 00:42:40,550
Five hundred million dollars?


650
00:42:41,690 --> 00:42:44,290
If you don't report his death,


651
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:45,890
the soon-to-be-elect chairman


652
00:42:45,960 --> 00:42:48,430
will file a lawsuit for damages
under the name of the foundation.


653
00:42:49,060 --> 00:42:52,830
Chairman Doh Jin-sol prevented
that from happening so far.


654
00:42:53,330 --> 00:42:56,470
What kind of relationship
did the chairman and my husband have?


655
00:43:09,380 --> 00:43:10,450
From what I know,


656
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:12,850
they've had a special relationship
for ten years,


657
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:16,290
after the chairman divorced
her British husband in Hong Kong.


658
00:43:17,120 --> 00:43:18,760
Mr. An established
a non-profit organization


659
00:43:18,820 --> 00:43:20,360
to establish the foundation


660
00:43:20,430 --> 00:43:22,800
and appointed Doh Jin-sol as the chairman.


661
00:43:24,060 --> 00:43:27,070
Everything was planned out by Mr. An.


662
00:43:28,330 --> 00:43:31,170
What about the CEO of Locanda Hotel,
Nam Ji-seon?


663
00:43:32,710 --> 00:43:35,670
She's the key investor
and the biggest victim of the debt.


664
00:43:35,740 --> 00:43:37,210
Due to the nature of a mutual fund,


665
00:43:37,280 --> 00:43:40,580
the investor's identity is not exposed,
so she hasn't been revealed.


666
00:43:41,150 --> 00:43:43,050
But for now, she must be holding
the greatest grudge


667
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,320
against Mr. An and the chairman.


668
00:43:49,020 --> 00:43:50,920
How can this happen?


669
00:43:51,690 --> 00:43:53,530
He never once mentioned anything...


670
00:43:54,590 --> 00:43:55,960
How could he let it come to this?


671
00:43:56,030 --> 00:43:59,200
Mr. An must've tried everything
he could to stop it,


672
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:01,700
but it probably was inevitable.


673
00:44:01,900 --> 00:44:04,100
That may be why he couldn't tell you.


674
00:44:06,210 --> 00:44:07,870
But reporting his death...


675
00:44:10,210 --> 00:44:13,380
Do we have to go this far?
At this point in time?


676
00:44:15,210 --> 00:44:18,450
Well, it's up to you to decide


677
00:44:18,520 --> 00:44:20,450
but only you can do it.


678
00:44:21,190 --> 00:44:22,890
Everything is in that flash drive.


679
00:44:44,710 --> 00:44:45,710
[Audio File]


680
00:44:47,980 --> 00:44:49,250
An audio file?


681
00:44:52,380 --> 00:44:56,160
[Audio File]


682
00:44:57,190 --> 00:44:58,460
[Yeo-wool.]


683
00:44:59,890 --> 00:45:01,960
[By the time you listen to this,]


684
00:45:02,490 --> 00:45:04,160
[I won't be there anymore.]


685
00:45:05,730 --> 00:45:09,270
[I'm sorry everything ended up like this
without letting you know.]


686
00:45:15,310 --> 00:45:17,840
[I can't dare
to ask for your forgiveness.]


687
00:45:20,310 --> 00:45:22,080
[But right now,]


688
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,880
[I have to cut you and Yi-chan
off from me]


689
00:45:26,450 --> 00:45:28,690
[and this is the only way.]


690
00:45:29,620 --> 00:45:31,360
[To completely remove myself.]


691
00:45:42,270 --> 00:45:44,800
[I don't want to drag you along
into this darkness anymore.]


692
00:45:46,040 --> 00:45:47,610
[This is my last request.]


693
00:45:50,410 --> 00:45:52,380
[Please let me go now.]


694
00:46:17,270 --> 00:46:18,500
[I'm sorry]


695
00:46:19,540 --> 00:46:20,770
[and I love you.]


696
00:46:22,070 --> 00:46:24,240
[Everything I did was for you.]


697
00:47:04,980 --> 00:47:07,020
What are you doing with the lights off?


698
00:47:11,590 --> 00:47:13,690
You said you didn't know the chairman.


699
00:47:15,390 --> 00:47:19,330
Well, bringing it up
didn't seem like a good idea.


700
00:47:20,270 --> 00:47:21,470
And it's all in the past.


701
00:47:22,600 --> 00:47:24,040
All in the past?


702
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:27,710
If it's all in the past,
why did you go to the hotel together?


703
00:47:28,140 --> 00:47:30,780
I saw everything.


704
00:47:30,840 --> 00:47:33,680
I saw you two going into the hotel,


705
00:47:33,750 --> 00:47:35,050
looking all lovey-dovey.


706
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:39,490
-Did you tail me?
-Is that what's important right now?


707
00:47:39,790 --> 00:47:42,290
Why did the police come looking for you?


708
00:47:42,350 --> 00:47:44,220
What did you do to the chairman?


709
00:47:45,790 --> 00:47:47,790
We'd better not see each other
for a while.


710
00:47:48,390 --> 00:47:50,200
-What?
-Let's take some time apart.


711
00:47:54,430 --> 00:47:57,470
What right do you have
to say that in this situation?


712
00:47:58,900 --> 00:48:01,140
I'm the one who won't see you.


713
00:48:01,570 --> 00:48:04,240
For a while? There's no need for that.


714
00:48:04,740 --> 00:48:06,250
Let's end things.


715
00:48:10,580 --> 00:48:11,620
You know,


716
00:48:12,480 --> 00:48:14,550
I wasn't proud of this,


717
00:48:15,250 --> 00:48:16,920
but at least I was sincere to you.


718
00:48:18,790 --> 00:48:20,060
But you...


719
00:48:21,130 --> 00:48:23,860
You just used and toyed with me
from start to finish,


720
00:48:23,930 --> 00:48:26,370
and now that you're in trouble,
you're going to back out?


721
00:48:27,230 --> 00:48:28,770
You jerk.


722
00:48:43,750 --> 00:48:46,550
-What about the Director?
-He's still at work.


723
00:48:55,230 --> 00:48:57,630
[Husband]


724
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,370
[The number you have dialed]


725
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:05,770
[is currently unavailable.
Please leave a message after--]


726
00:49:07,570 --> 00:49:09,580
Check his schedule from tomorrow
and report back to me.


727
00:49:09,980 --> 00:49:12,080
And check if something's going on
at the hospital.


728
00:49:13,080 --> 00:49:15,380
-Be discreet so he doesn't notice.
-Yes, ma'am.


729
00:49:21,150 --> 00:49:23,720
[Nam Ji-seon]


730
00:49:31,730 --> 00:49:33,630
It'll sting a little.


731
00:49:34,900 --> 00:49:37,140
Make sure it doesn't hurt, Doctor.


732
00:49:50,150 --> 00:49:51,520
This is Song Yeo-wool.


733
00:49:52,750 --> 00:49:54,020
About what we discussed yesterday...


734
00:49:55,120 --> 00:49:58,360
I'll let you know
as soon as I gather my thoughts.


735
00:50:04,400 --> 00:50:06,030
[Death Registration Form
Name: An Ji-yong]


736
00:50:07,770 --> 00:50:10,440
[Death Registration Form
Name: An Ji-yong]


737
00:50:18,240 --> 00:50:19,810
[Song Yeo-wool]


738
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:43,940
Yi-chan.


739
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:48,410
Why don't we move back to Seoul?


740
00:50:48,540 --> 00:50:49,570
Why?


741
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:53,050
Because this place


742
00:50:54,010 --> 00:50:56,180
reminds me too much of your dad.


743
00:50:56,250 --> 00:50:58,680
Do you not like remembering Dad?


744
00:51:02,090 --> 00:51:03,360
He probably


745
00:51:03,890 --> 00:51:06,060
doesn't want to see me like this.


746
00:51:06,120 --> 00:51:09,700
You said he'll never disappear
as long as we remember him.


747
00:51:12,860 --> 00:51:15,470
I thought everything would be okay


748
00:51:15,530 --> 00:51:18,000
if we moved here.


749
00:51:19,570 --> 00:51:21,940
I don't think he can rest in peace


750
00:51:22,570 --> 00:51:24,280
if I keep holding onto him like this.


751
00:51:24,440 --> 00:51:26,650
I guess
you don't feel at ease here either.


752
00:51:27,210 --> 00:51:29,380
Mom, I'm happy if you're happy.


753
00:51:29,610 --> 00:51:31,550
If something makes you unhappy,
I don't like it either.


754
00:51:31,980 --> 00:51:35,720
If I can see your happy face
when we move there, then I'm all for it.


755
00:51:39,120 --> 00:51:40,630
Thanks, son.


756
00:51:41,530 --> 00:51:42,590
Yes!


757
00:52:15,130 --> 00:52:17,200
What brings you by?
There's no practice today.


758
00:52:27,170 --> 00:52:28,940
I'm sorry, Mr. Oh Soon-sang.


759
00:52:29,110 --> 00:52:30,580
You have nothing to apologize for.


760
00:52:31,310 --> 00:52:34,610
I just do things because I get paid.


761
00:52:36,210 --> 00:52:38,720
I think we're going to leave this place.


762
00:52:39,720 --> 00:52:43,220
Too many things have happened
since we moved here.


763
00:52:43,860 --> 00:52:47,090
I wanted to find out
what really happened to him.


764
00:52:47,830 --> 00:52:49,690
I wanted to uncover the truth,


765
00:52:51,030 --> 00:52:53,030
but it's all pointless now.


766
00:52:54,100 --> 00:52:55,600
I should just let him go


767
00:52:57,070 --> 00:52:58,940
and put an end to everything
once and for all.


768
00:53:03,480 --> 00:53:05,940
Well, whatever you decide to do,


769
00:53:07,150 --> 00:53:11,220
make sure you do
what gives you peace of mind.


770
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:14,520
Just because you've decided to let go,
it doesn't mean the person is gone.


771
00:53:15,620 --> 00:53:18,620
And by the same token, holding on
doesn't mean the person is yours,


772
00:53:19,420 --> 00:53:22,290
so leave and move to a place
where you can be


773
00:53:23,560 --> 00:53:24,730
at peace.


774
00:53:29,330 --> 00:53:32,100
Does this mean
our contract is really terminated now?


775
00:53:43,980 --> 00:53:45,220
That's it.


776
00:53:45,780 --> 00:53:47,790
The ones that need to be lit
taste much better.


777
00:53:51,660 --> 00:53:52,890
I'm home!


778
00:53:53,120 --> 00:53:54,460
My gosh, honey!


779
00:53:55,630 --> 00:53:59,870
What's gotten into you?
You're never home this early.


780
00:54:04,440 --> 00:54:06,540
What is going on here?


781
00:54:06,610 --> 00:54:08,870
I had nothing going on today,


782
00:54:08,940 --> 00:54:11,640
so I figured I should come home early
to see you and my son.


783
00:54:11,710 --> 00:54:12,710
I see.


784
00:54:12,780 --> 00:54:16,210
And Chef Jung happens
to be free today as well.


785
00:54:16,820 --> 00:54:19,820
You mentioned a few times
that we should invite him over.


786
00:54:20,190 --> 00:54:21,090
What?


787
00:54:22,050 --> 00:54:25,460
Right, I did say that.


788
00:54:26,420 --> 00:54:28,560
Hello, Chef Jung.


789
00:54:28,890 --> 00:54:32,530
I can't believe you just showed up
without even calling first.


790
00:54:33,430 --> 00:54:35,530
I apologize for coming unannounced.


791
00:54:36,000 --> 00:54:38,370
-Thank you for inviting me.
-Gosh, it's my pleasure.


792
00:54:41,470 --> 00:54:43,440
-Daddy? Dad!
-Goodness.


793
00:54:43,510 --> 00:54:44,640
-My son!
-Are you insane?


794
00:54:44,710 --> 00:54:46,780
-How have you been?
-Get out.


795
00:54:47,010 --> 00:54:48,410
You've gotten chubby.


796
00:54:49,510 --> 00:54:50,950
What about my game console, Dad?


797
00:54:51,020 --> 00:54:52,680
Right, I brought it.
I'll give it to you later.


798
00:54:52,750 --> 00:54:53,950
You're the best, Dad.


799
00:54:54,020 --> 00:54:56,150
-Say hello.
-Hello.


800
00:55:00,560 --> 00:55:01,660
Darn it.


801
00:55:03,660 --> 00:55:06,730
Right. A detective called me earlier,
so I spoke to him.


802
00:55:07,000 --> 00:55:08,700
A detective?


803
00:55:09,000 --> 00:55:10,440
Why did a detective call you?


804
00:55:10,500 --> 00:55:12,070
Because of Chairman Doh.


805
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:15,440
I think they're just interviewing everyone
as a formality.


806
00:55:22,010 --> 00:55:23,110
Gosh...


807
00:55:23,580 --> 00:55:28,090
Chef Jung, are you seeing anyone?


808
00:55:29,150 --> 00:55:31,820
Sorry? Well...


809
00:55:32,260 --> 00:55:33,590
No, not at the moment.


810
00:55:33,660 --> 00:55:35,230
Come on! I don't believe you.


811
00:55:35,730 --> 00:55:40,300
There's no way
women would leave you alone.


812
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:43,170
-Right?
-What? Well...


813
00:55:43,370 --> 00:55:44,700
I don't know.


814
00:55:44,770 --> 00:55:46,570
I get it. This is a small town


815
00:55:46,640 --> 00:55:48,310
where people watch everything
about everyone.


816
00:55:49,010 --> 00:55:52,610
Rumors can't be tamed, you know.


817
00:55:52,680 --> 00:55:56,250
You can be slammed to the ground
once malicious rumors spread.


818
00:55:58,080 --> 00:55:59,220
Don't you agree?


819
00:55:59,990 --> 00:56:02,320
Right, I guess.


820
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:08,060
Let's see.


821
00:56:09,730 --> 00:56:12,060
How about I set you up with someone?


822
00:56:13,500 --> 00:56:16,130
What's your type?


823
00:56:18,240 --> 00:56:19,670
No, it's okay.


824
00:56:19,740 --> 00:56:21,410
Come on. Don't be shy.


825
00:56:21,770 --> 00:56:25,080
A chef who appreciates fine flavors
needs a fine girl.


826
00:56:29,250 --> 00:56:30,950
Here. Have another drink.


827
00:56:31,280 --> 00:56:32,720
Oh, no. We're out.


828
00:56:32,780 --> 00:56:35,620
My gosh. I'll go get another bottle.


829
00:56:35,790 --> 00:56:36,890
Give me a minute.


830
00:56:37,920 --> 00:56:38,990
Sure.


831
00:56:50,100 --> 00:56:52,400
Have you lost your mind?
How could you come here?


832
00:56:52,470 --> 00:56:54,070
I didn't want to come here either.


833
00:56:54,140 --> 00:56:56,510
Go back before he gets suspicious.


834
00:56:57,480 --> 00:56:58,480
Wait.


835
00:56:59,110 --> 00:57:00,380
We need to finish our conversation.


836
00:57:00,450 --> 00:57:01,650
What conversation?


837
00:57:03,280 --> 00:57:06,320
About stabbing me in the back
by trying to steal the trademark


838
00:57:06,380 --> 00:57:08,350
and get another woman to invest in you?


839
00:57:08,420 --> 00:57:10,620
-No, you got the wrong idea.
-Don't lie to my face!


840
00:57:10,720 --> 00:57:12,720
Do you want to die?


841
00:57:12,790 --> 00:57:15,360
Get out of my house at once,
before I hit you with this.


842
00:57:16,460 --> 00:57:17,630
Do-yeong.


843
00:57:25,270 --> 00:57:26,940
What's taking you so long?


844
00:57:27,010 --> 00:57:31,080
Well, I wasn't sure which wine
would be the best.


845
00:57:31,140 --> 00:57:32,280
It took me a while to pick one.


846
00:57:33,780 --> 00:57:37,450
This is the same one.
Are you okay with this?


847
00:57:37,920 --> 00:57:39,220
Yes, it's fine.


848
00:57:39,950 --> 00:57:41,520
Where's Chef Jung? Did you see him?


849
00:57:41,590 --> 00:57:44,190
What? Right!


850
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:46,760
He said the wine gave him a headache.


851
00:57:46,830 --> 00:57:48,090
He stepped out just now.


852
00:57:48,230 --> 00:57:49,860
-Let's go.
-Okay.


853
00:58:08,110 --> 00:58:14,620
[Southern Jeju is expecting heavy rain
of up to 50mm per hour.]


854
00:58:14,690 --> 00:58:17,860
[Heavy rain accompanied by strong winds,
thunder, and lightning]


855
00:58:17,920 --> 00:58:21,460
[is expected through the night
into early tomorrow morning.]


856
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:26,990
Mom?


857
00:59:56,820 --> 00:59:58,490
Mom!


858
01:00:05,730 --> 01:00:06,760
Yi-chan.


859
01:00:08,970 --> 01:00:10,000
Yi-chan!


860
01:00:11,470 --> 01:00:12,570
Mommy is here!


861
01:00:17,440 --> 01:00:18,440
Yi-chan!


862
01:00:18,980 --> 01:00:20,650
Yi-chan, what happened?


863
01:00:20,710 --> 01:00:22,850
What's wrong? What is it?


864
01:00:26,050 --> 01:00:27,390
Did the lightning scare you?


865
01:00:27,450 --> 01:00:30,220
It's okay. Let's get back inside.


866
01:00:52,210 --> 01:00:55,250
What? What just happened?


867
01:00:56,110 --> 01:00:58,120
What was that?


868
01:00:58,980 --> 01:01:00,590
What's going on?


869
01:01:02,020 --> 01:01:03,050
Wait a second.


870
01:01:36,050 --> 01:01:38,790
[High Class]


871
01:01:39,060 --> 01:01:41,130
I'm not going to register
my husband's death.


872
01:01:41,230 --> 01:01:44,030
[I won't use his death
to give myself closure.]


873
01:01:44,100 --> 01:01:45,630
[Why do you get to decide that?]


874
01:01:45,700 --> 01:01:47,600
I'm his legal wife.


875
01:01:48,070 --> 01:01:50,400
-Answer me, Yi-chan.
[-Last night must've shocked him.]


876
01:01:50,470 --> 01:01:52,100
[He stopped speaking.]


877
01:01:53,070 --> 01:01:55,310
[Was it you?
Did you do that to that house?]


878
01:01:55,370 --> 01:01:57,140
[Did you hate me so much?]


879
01:01:57,210 --> 01:01:59,280
[So much that you threw a rock
in the middle of the night?]


880
01:01:59,340 --> 01:02:01,150
[Move out of that house immediately.]


881
01:02:01,380 --> 01:02:03,080
[I saw someone]


882
01:02:03,150 --> 01:02:04,850
[watching your house.]


